content:
Create a Block from a Dialog Group

Export a dialog group as the basis for a bot block. You can package bot blocks and share them between orgs or on AppExchange.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Before a dialog group can become a block, you must remove unsupported elements from the bot version. These elements include:

Transfer actions: A block can’t contain the Transfer to Agent Rule action.
Einstein Intent Sets: A block can’t contain a dialog intent that is linked to an Einstein Intent Set.
Structured content in Enhanced Bots.

From the Einstein Bots main page, open the bot you want to use to create the block. Identify the dialog group you want to use to create the block. Click the dropdown and then click Export as Block.

Give your block a name, and set a primary language and any secondary languages. Optionally, add a permission set to your block so any bots created from your template have access to required resources. Click Create Block.
title: Creating Einstein Bots Blocks
